      "writtenOn": "2020-04-13T12:12:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "See previous comments in the CL. Basically by the way we store GrD3DTextureResourceInfos as a union on GrBackendTexture, it can cause us to create and uninitialized GrD3DTextureResourceInfo. When we later go to initialize it with assign function, the unique_ptr doesn\u0027t have a nullptr but some random value in it. Thus it will try to unref that ptr which isn\u0027t good. I suppose we could use release on the unique_ptr but we\u0027d still need the isThisValid parameter passed in. The argument is if we\u0027re already do some manual ref tracking should we just go all the way it instead of managing some hybrid versoin? Personally I am happy with either approach.",
      "parentUuid": "21212276_7f98260e",
